            CHAP. XII. Wherein are contained Theologicall Aphorismes concerning the GOSPELL.
            1 THe Gospell is Parallell to the Law.
            
            2 The Doctrines of both have a celestiall Originall.
            3 In both, there is life eternall promised: but in a different manner.
            4 In the Law it is promised to those that performe perfect obedience: but in the Gospell it is promised to those that truely beleeve on Christ.
            5 The Doctrines of both are to

be propounded unto us in the Church.
            6 For both of them are of necessarie use in the conversion of man.
