                     •
                  morensis (in speculo vit. Human. Lib. 2. Cap. 3.) and Nicholas de Cleman. (Lib. de Ruin. &amp; Reparat. Ecclesiae) whose testimonie is most true on this part.
            90 By these and the like abuses without doubt it is so come to passe, that the most wholesome part of Ecclesiasticall Discipline is at this day fallen to decay and come to ruine. See other causes thereof in Luthers Commentaries (Supr. 3. Joel. Tom. 4. Jen. Fol. 801. &amp;c.) Reade them and perpend them.
            91 O Christ thou which thrustest forth Labourers into thy harvest, Thrust in thy sickle, and reape: for the time is come for thee to

